                  </persName>
            , pawnbroker in London-street. On the 13th of September, the prisoner pawned a pair of plated candlesticks for 20 s., and two salts were pawned in July for 25 s.; and afterwards I advanced 10 s. more, and on the 31st of August, 10 s. more, making 2 l. 5 s. I never saw him till he pawned the salts. When he brought the candlesticks, he said he was a manufacturer - he gave the name of 
               <persName id="t18221023-23-person329">
                  John 
                  Wittingham
               <interp inst="t18221023-23-person329" type="surname" value="Wittingham"></interp>
